## Test 4: Check MAVSDK connection

Modify `Drone.cpp` to print the connection result:

```cpp
#include <iostream>

...

const auto result = m_mavsdk.add_any_connection("udpin://0.0.0.0:14540");

std::cout << "Connection Result: "
          << static_cast<int>(result)
          << std::endl;
```

> **Note:** For MAVSDK 3.x, use `udpin://0.0.0.0:14540` instead of the deprecated `udp://:14540`.

Run the app again.

Expected:

```text
Connection Result: 0
```

`0` means **Success**.

---

## Test 5: Verify PX4 discovery

Add:

```cpp
auto system = m_mavsdk.first_autopilot(10.0);

if (system) {
    std::cout << "PX4 Found!" << std::endl;
} else {
    std::cout << "No PX4 Found!" << std::endl;
}
```

Expected:

```text
PX4 Found!
```

